{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.10",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 10",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 10 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:1",
      "text": "“ My soul is weary of my life. I will give free course to my complaint. I will speak in the bitterness of my soul.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:2",
      "text": "I will tell God, ‘ Do not condemn me. Show me why you contend with me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:3",
      "text": "Is it good to you that you should oppress, that you should despise the work of your hands, and smile on the counsel of the wicked?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:4",
      "text": "Do you have eyes of flesh? Or do you see as man sees?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:5",
      "text": "Are your days as the days of mortals, or your years as man ’s years,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:6",
      "text": "that you inquire after my iniquity, and search after my sin?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:7",
      "text": "Although you know that I am not wicked, there is no one who can deliver out of your hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:8",
      "text": "“‘ Your hands have framed me and fashioned me altogether, yet you destroy me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:9",
      "text": "Remember, I beg you, that you have fashioned me as clay. Will you bring me into dust again?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:10",
      "text": "Haven’t you poured me out like milk, and curdled me like cheese?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:11",
      "text": "You have clothed me with skin and flesh, and knit me together with bones and sinews.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:12",
      "text": "You have granted me life and loving kindness. Your visitation has preserved my spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:13",
      "text": "Yet you hid these things in your heart. I know that this is with you:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:14",
      "text": "if I sin, then you mark me. You will not acquit me from my iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:15",
      "text": "If I am wicked, woe to me. If I am righteous, I still will not lift up my head, being filled with disgrace, and conscious of my affliction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:16",
      "text": "If my head is held high, you hunt me like a lion. Again you show yourself powerful to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:17",
      "text": "You renew your witnesses against me, and increase your indignation on me. Changes and warfare are with me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:18",
      "text": "“‘ Why, then, have you brought me out of the womb? I wish I had given up the spirit, and no eye had seen me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:19",
      "text": "I should have been as though I had not been. I should have been carried from the womb to the grave.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:20",
      "text": "Aren’t my days few? Stop! Leave me alone, that I may find a little comfort,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:21",
      "text": "before I go where I will not return from, to the land of darkness and of the shadow of death;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.10.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:22",
      "text": "the land dark as midnight, of the shadow of death, without any order, where the light is as midnight.’”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
